  "prompt": "How do you make the best tequila shot?",
  "response": "Making the best tequila shot involves selecting the right tequila and pairing it with complementary flavors. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### Ingredients:\n1. **Tequila**: Choose quality 100% agave tequila. Options include:\n   - **Blanco** (unaged) for a pure, vibrant flavor\n   - **Reposado** (aged up to a year) for a smoother taste\n   - **A\u00f1ejo** (aged longer) for deeper flavors\n\n2. **Salt** (optional): Coarse sea salt or kosher salt.\n\n3. **Lime wedges**: Fresh lime is traditional, but you can also use oranges or other citrus.\n\n### Equipment:\n- Shot glass\n- Small plate (for salt, if using)\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Choose Your Tequila**: Select a good quality tequila. For a classic shot, Blanco is often preferred, but feel free to experiment with Reposado or A\u00f1ejo.\n\n2. **Salt the Rim (optional)**:\n   - Pour some salt onto a small plate.\n   - Rub a lime wedge along the rim of the shot glass to moisten it.\n   - Dip the rim of the glass into the salt to coat it lightly.\n\n3. **Pour the Shot**: Pour about 1.5 oz (a standard shot) of tequila into the shot glass.\n\n4. **Prepare the Lime Wedge**: Cut a lime into wedges. You can serve the wedge on the side of the shot glass.\n\n### Taking the Shot:\n\n1. **Lick the Salt** (if using):\n   - If you've salted the rim, lick the salt off the rim of the shot glass before taking the shot.\n\n2. **Drink the Shot**: \n   - In one quick motion, raise the shot glass, take the shot of tequila, and then bite into the lime wedge immediately after swallowing.\n\n3. **Savor the Flavor**: Enjoy the flavors and aftertaste of the tequila.\n\n### Tips:\n- Experiment with different tequilas to find your favorite for shots.\n- Using fresh lime is key; avoid bottled lime juice for best taste.\n- Drinking water after the shot can help cleanse your palate.\n\nRemember to drink responsibly!",
